    "comment": "Rationale: Rationale: NLGN1; neuroligin 1 is a postsynaptic protein. Neurexin-1beta is a presynaptic protein (Fig.4, 6, 7). These proteins are shown to mediate cell-cell adhesion (Fig.2). Together this means that these proteins are involved in 'synapse adhesion between pre- and post-synapse (GO:0099560)'. The relevance of this interaction is shown in the ability of these two protein to be able to induce pre- and postsynaptic differentiation (Fig.6, 7 and ticket #2745).\n\nFig.2: \"Inactive neuroligin mutants are impaired in neuroligin/neurexin mediated cell adhesion\"\nFig.6: \"Induction of neurexin clustering and presynaptic differentiation by purified neuroligin.\". Experimental description: - \"Cerebellar granule cells were isolated from mice ...\"\n- The species of overexpressed NLGN1; neuroligin 1 and neurexin proteins are not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (dd. 2/3/2018, peter.scheiffele@unibas.ch). Answer was:\n\n\"Hi Pim,\nAll cDNAs were originally cloned from mouse (Scheiffele et al., Cell, 2000)\nBest,\nPeter\"",
